                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d390">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">863.51 Relief Credits/224: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Swenson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Oslo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-05-06T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 6, 1930—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 6—9:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8. The Department’s telegram No. 93, April 15, American Embassy at London.
                    Foreign Office informs me that the Norwegian Government has agreed to
                    subordinate the lien in question on the conditions named in Sir Frederick
                    Leith-Ross’ letter to Austrian Minister in London, dated April 15, last.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Swenson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
